node.text:
Today, we turn 171. In an annual Founders Day tradition, @utahalumni honors those with the Distinguished Alumni Award.

One of this year’s recipients is Ronald G. Coleman BS’66 PHD’80, an emeritus professor of history and ethnic studies at the U. As a student, Coleman helped lead @utahfootball to its 1964 Liberty Bowl victory. He is a nationally recognized scholar of African American history and was recently honored with a Humanitarian Award by the Inclusion Center for Community and Justice. Coleman is currently an advisor to the @uofubcc and advisor to the vice president for @uofuedi.
•
#UofU #universityofutah #UtahFootball

node.text: Students, staff & faculty are encouraged to take part in the free asymptomatic #COVID19 testing program on campus. The more tests, the more we can help reduce the spread of coronavirus in the community, and the sooner we can get on with life. The manager for the #UofU Covid-19 testing program, Cameron Wright, @uofustudentgov vice president @ayanaamaechi talk about the program and answer some FAQs.

node.title: Help Reduce the Spread of COVID-19 — GET TESTED!

node.text:
Each day frontline medical workers put their lives at risk to ensure the well-being of #COVID19 patients.

This video, produced by @UBusiness & the @sorensonimpact Center's #utahHEROproject, sheds light on the daily battle #healthcareworkers have faced during the pandemic.
•
#UofU #universityofutah

node.title: The toll of Covid-19 on frontline medical workers

node.text:
This spring we teamed up with the @accessfund and @renan_ozturk to survey climbers who visit Indian Creek to gauge visitation and explore conservation & education strategies to ensure a sustainable future for climbing in the area.

Based on those results, the @accessfund will have climbing stewards on the ground to help mitigate human impact and protect the natural habitat. 

📸: @renan_ozturk 
•
#UofU #IndianCreek #UofUoutdoors #utahisrad
